<br>
As I see it we have alot of hypocritical thoughts and two sided arguements.  Now, alot of talk has been about the pride in earning something and the spirit of the rathe.  Well, why is it that I see items in the bazaar for sale that come from zones that I KNOW only a few guilds can get to and these items are for sale for UNGODLY amounts of money to anyone in the bazaar.  Wouldn't it be fair to say that the people that purchase these items didnt earn it on their own and are not  contributing to the ideal of pride in ownership.  That is, after all, what we are talking about...earning flags in the &quot;proper&quot; way to go into these zones.  Seems kinda hypocritical that it is ok for some people to SELL items to people that didnt earn them(wait that should be ok because it is economics isnt it?).  Seems like you are pushing the fact that it is ok for people to get loot they didnt work for(I.E. killing the mob that dropped it) but it is not ok for them to find another convention for getting loot(I.E.  grouping with other guilds for flags).<br>
<br>
Also, I may be minunderstanding the intent, but we are not talking about killing Aary to get a guild on the NToV rotation, we are talking about getting a large group of individual's flagged for exp zones, at least that is what I read in the initial post.  It is a problem that the server population has a large amount of 60+ characters and there is such a small amount of 60+ exp zones.  <br>
<br>
I can understand that point of &quot;we got here by earning it, and we get PISSED off when you dont earn it&quot;, but that leads back to my original point &quot;it is ok for you to buy this weapon from me for 150kpp(that dropped in a zone that you cannot get to much less kill a mob in), although I know you didnt earn it, I am gaining from it, so it is all good.  But it is not ok for you to get flagged for a zone that might give me more lfg time, or cause me an occasional death.&quot;  I feel that is the crux of this arguement.   <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.wrjm.com/harrysig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=derokspineripper>Derok Spineripper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(2/24/03 11:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=111>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Moot Point?</span><hr size=1> I'm at work right now, so I can't confirm this myself.  But someone posted the new patch message from today's patch, and this part seemed applicable to the topic at hand.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>** Gameplay **<br>
<br>
We've adjusted the entry requirements for some Planes of Power zones. Several of these zones required each character to complete a quest before gaining entry. We've relaxed this requirement somewhat as follows:<br>
<br>
* A raid with 32 or more members can enter a locked plane provided that 85% of the raiders have finished the entry quest. This means a raid group can bring along some friends who haven't completed the quest.<br>
<br>
* Characters who haven't done the entry quest must stay with their raid while they are in the locked zone. If these characters leave the raid for more than three minutes, they will be transported out to the Plane of Tranquility.<br>
<br>
* Using this method does not grant permanent access to the locked zone. If a character wants permanent, unescorted access to a locked zone then they must still complete the quest. The goal of this change is to allow raiding groups to bring along a few friends who haven't been able to complete the quests, but still wish to help with the raid.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>- Several of the flagging events will now only give out a maximum of 72 flags each time they are completed.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
- The dialogue boxes for resurrection and translocation will remain for 5 minutes instead of 1 hour.<br>
- Increased the maximum number of members on ignore and friends lists to 100.<br>
- Made some adjustments to the Halls of Honor alternate entry quest that should make it more friendly.<br>
- The horse buff icon will no longer show up for characters using non-Luclin models.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
