<br>
1)  As a social contract, what is good for the server ?<br>
<br>
Valid question.  This is what the discussion chould be focused on, imho.  Is teaming up an 'abuse of the rules' ?<br>
<br>
2)  Has something been earned, is it deserved ?<br>
<br>
I don't think this is a valid question at all.  I am not a big fan of -players- deciding what other players deserve, based on moral definitions of 'deserving'.  I went from soloing to duoing without losing 'pride'.  I went from duoing to grouping without losing 'pride'.  I went from grouping to a guild without losing 'pride'.  Who decided that was the limit ?<br>
<br>
It's not as if you 'earn' anything alone, anyway.  You bring a raid's worth of people to earn it with you.  If you choose to draw the line at cooperation within your guild, that's certainly your choice.<br>
<br>
While there have been some very intelligent arguments made about what people deserve and what they do not...ultimately they are just rationalizations for, at worse, personal agendas and, at best, pushing individual's arbitrary views of how everyone else 'should do things'.<br>
<br>
- Uusk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karadin>Karadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NB-GM<BR>
