<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> I don't get your reply Karadin.. All you did was back up what I had said. I didn't say anyone has actually carried out these actions but have implied it. Your above quote says you have made such implying remarks. /shrug.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Then read it again.  You imply that threats have been made to permakill the flag mobs.  I will say it very clearly here, I have not made such threats, overtly or implied.  My only mention of that kind of action is to retort people who offer the argument, that “it’s not against SOE rules to team up”.  That’s all.  I’m not implying anything, I am pointing out the problem of taking advantage of the spirit of the rotations (i.e. having your kills protected by an orderly turn system that shares content among guilds/alliances who are able to kill the same content without the strife of an FFA system) while trying to manipulate that these mobs, which normally would be on rotation, by teaming up to get access to content they couldn’t get to on their own.  As my fellow dorf Baysar says, you can’t have it both ways.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Not all agree with this, hence all the debate. The spirit of the RTA is talked about often yet it's not apparant.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So far I only see one guild disagreeing with what has been discussed here.  Now what I find interesting is that you (specifically Jurassic and Baysar) can claim BotS/Tindi/NB are being “protectionist” and are only frowning upon this because they don’t want to share the higher tier zones with other people.  However, you are ignoring the position of LoM, SotE, VoF, and other guilds of similar “status” for lack of a better word.  None of them have access to Tactics, yet you see them evaluating the idea of teaming up and frowning on it as well.  Why?  I suspect it has a lot to do with the issues I have posted about in this thread, guild pride and accomplishment.<br>
<br>
I’ve also seen you post about how, because they won’t see the higher end of PoP they might as well quit EQ.  I ask then, should everyone who hasn’t been to N ToV also quit?  Or Emperor?  Or Vex Thal?  These are all high end content that most of the Rathe guilds will never see, and cannot team up to go to.  Why do you figure PoP should be any different?  Just because United Necros will never see Vex Thal or Plane of Time is not a reason to quit EQ.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Zaken,<br>
<br>
