If they just want xp in Tactics, then go get the Diaku quest reward – a flag for Tactics.  Killing Behemoth is required for further progression in PoP, the access to Tactics xp (no better than PoV badlands, but with less idiots atm) is merely a side effect.  The point is, if this was N ToV, two guilds teaming up to beat Aary but wanting to remain solo on other rotations WOULD be a direct and obvious rotation violation.  If Behemoth or Aerin Dar were on rotation, same thing.  That is why it’s against the spirit, but not the letter of the rotation system.  Killing mobs one can’t kill on one’s own by teaming is like inviting members of your older brother’s farm team to win your little league championship game.  Yay, you get the trophy, but did you win anything?<br>
