Uusk,<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp At how many “individuals” does it become a valid group view?  I see Tindi, SotE, LoM, NB, BotS, VoF, all saying that teaming is against the spirit of the rotation system.  And I see one or two guilds of similar “status” (again, lack of a better word, but what a L 20-30 guild thinks of how PoP is handled is irrelevant imo) saying that teaming, while not something to be proud of, is not a bad thing either.  I also disagree with your premise that any subjective or objective basis for “what is deserved” is about any one individual’s arbitrary views.  The rule about not teaming on rotation mobs has been in place since BotS and KEG worked out the first rotation on Trak – KEG wasn’t allowed to bring MFH or CIW members to their Trak attempts.  It has continued thus for three years.  The only distinguisher you can make is the technicality, and yes it’s a technicality, that these mobs aren’t on rotation (although we can all agree they fall under the same category of 3-7 day spawning rare boss mobs for many guilds).  It has been the server’s social contract for going on three year’s now, and until recently, wasn’t broken. <p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net/images/ezboard/sig-small.gif&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Karadin Firethorne&lt;br&gt;Assassin of The Rathe&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net&quot;&gt;Noble Blade&lt;/a&gt; <br>
