<br>
Which would be just as bad.  Teaming is teaming isn’t it?  Why limit it to two smallish guilds or two medium size?  Nevertheless, revision of analogy:  Killing mobs one can’t kill on one’s own by teaming is like inviting members of your cousin’s little league team to help win your little league championship game.  Moral of the story: it’s not your team doing the killing, and thus your team didn’t win the championship, nor should they get the rewards for having won it, since they didn’t.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> This is another example of what I meant by two issues getting intertwined. I am under the impression that RTA was set up to ensure that guilds have equal shots at raid level mobs, not as a moral reward system.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That’s just it, it’s not two issues, it’s one issue, that certain guilds are looking to manipulate the spirit of the rotations through a technical loophole that these mobs aren’t actually on rotation, but under past historic precedent, would be.  I’m sorry you have a misguided idea of what the RTA was created for, but it was not so that United Necros has an equal shot at Plane of Time/VT/ST/VP.  It was setup so that all guilds/alliances that can actually kill any particular raid-level content can do so with as few headaches as possible.  In that, it IS a moral reward system, based on the agreed upon “morals” of the majority of the raid-capable guilds on the server (what LOIO folks think about PoP/Ssra rotations is beyond relevance).  In order to be an alliance for one mob on rotation you have to be an alliance for ALL rotations, not just the ones you pick and choose.  LoM/FK had to make a choice, either team up and have access to half the KT loot between them and share Sev loot as well, or split their Alliance and get their own full shares.  Trying to treat PoP mobs any differently is just trying to skirt that issue and abuse a loophole.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp You can drop the whole pride issue as merely a side topic, and disregard it entirely – it was merely offered as a possible reason for why others haven’t tried this before, not as the sum of the argument.  However, what you cannot disregard is that the RTA is a *player-made* system on the Rathe that goes beyond SOE’s rules, and thus IS about enforcing group views.  So when someone says “Hey, its not against the rules from SOE”, even if they’re right, its irrelevant.  They are still abusing the *player-made* system – taking advantage of the protections and guarantees it provides, while taking unfair advantage of loopholes to their own benefit.  It’s not against SOE rules for NB to kill Cursed tonight, but it IS against our server conventions, because NB is not up on rotation.  I am also not allowed to team up with Tindi to kill Rallos Zek, because it would be exploiting the spirit of the rotations.  How can one not see the exploitation of being able to keep two separate guilds for all those mobs that are trivial to you, but then getting mutual access to content that is beyond you?  It wouldn’t strengthen any Tindi/NB joint Rallos Raid argument to say “Hey, BOTS xps in the elemental planes, so we’re just gonna kill RZ together a few times to get new xp spots”.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The RTA is an accomplishment, not because of some utopian nature wherein guilds forego the loot dropped from rare mobs out of some misformed charity complex – it is an accomplishment because it deals very realistically with the issues of sharing content and does so in a very fair and systematic way.  That is to say, what makes our community special, is not that we all stand back and watch 4+ small guilds try the Avatar of War until they beat him, but that we are able to share very limited resources that realistically factors in our collective greed.  Abusing that system by teaming up to beat new content, but retaining separate guild status on other rotations should be a very obvious violation of the principles of that system.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> I can certainly see how teaming up on a rotation mob could be abused. Theoretically, you could split a large guild into 5 small guilds, have them all assist each other and get on the rotation 5 times as often. The question really should be &quot;Is that, in EFFECT, what is happening here ?&quot;.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I hadn’t wanted to use the old Aegirson argument that you pointed out, wherein NB could split into 4 guilds for Velious content, team up as 2 guilds for Luclin content, and then team up with Tindi for PoP content to min/max our loot/content intake, because it seems fairly obvious.  Yes that is exactly what 2-3 guilds teaming up to beat Behemoth is doing – remaining 2-3 guilds for purposes of server loot resources, but teaming up for new server loot resources they can’t get to as separate entities.  If they need to join up to do it, then fine, but join up for all rotations, even if they are “trivial”.  After all, that is what the big guilds have to do – they don’t get 2-3 helpings of Velious/Luclin content to equip their larger numbers.  So a new semi-alliance has access to content they would not have otherwise gained, and yet gets 2+ helpings of older content each, while the larger guilds now have to share content with people who shouldn’t be there (possibly “yet”, but possibly ever), and still only get half the loot they could have if they were 2+ guilds allied only for PoP. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> I think a lot of the arguments fall through if you look at it only in the light of &quot;Is it abusing the system and giving one or two guilds an advantage ?&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Your premise is weak, as it follows the unethical argument, that as long as everyone is allowed to exploit this, it isn’t a problem.  Taking twice the loot out of old world rotations, but teaming solely for PoP mobs abuses the system and gives an advantage over those who don’t do the same.  A good analogy, is the one I used in an above post:  In an FPS game, if we’re all using bot programs to rack up high kill scores, is this abusive?  Your answer would seem to be no, since we all have access to it.  My answer would be, yes, it is a problem, because you have just removed any possible accomplishment.  Also, please note, it is not against Id’s rules to use a bot program on any server you host, but you try getting legit players to come to your server if they know you run bots.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sandalorn,<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> feel nervous that the RTA has become less about giving equal opportunity to smaller guilds. .quote]<br>
<br>
It’s a fact of life that the RTA has never been about giving equal opportunity to smaller guilds.  NB will *never* get the same opportunity that BOTS had killing Rallos Zek.  We’ve never had the same opportunities on any of the mobs we’ve done, because by the time we got there, there was already at least one guild killing whatever it was.  That’s the disadvantage of not being first, or third, or seventeenth.  The guys who were first, third, or seventeenth have an advantage of already knowing how to kill it, and the second, fourth, and eighteenth aren’t going to get unrestricted access to a mob that is already being killed by many people.  <br>
<br>
The RTA is about getting equal *treatment* once you kill something.  That once you prove you can kill a certain mob, the remaining guilds will respect your spot on the rotation and agree not to kill your mob on your turn.<br>
<br>
The basis for alliances on rotations being an all or nothing affair is as old as the RTA and planar calendar.  It is not some new invention for any “moral scratching <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net/images/ezboard/sig-small.gif&quot; align=&quot;left&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Karadin Firethorne&lt;br&gt;Assassin of The Rathe&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.noble-blade.net&quot;&gt;Noble Blade&lt;/a&gt; <br>
