I know I previously stated that I had said my piece and my peace, but I can't stay away from what is being said here.<br>
<br>
Karadin, Emil and all others...<br>
<br>
Someone tell me WHY a mob that only allows ACCESS to a zone and that members of 2 (or more) guilds teamed up to take down said mob ruins the integrity, ethics, moral standards set forth within the RTA?  How does 1 mob that has no loot, except for letting someone have access to another zone, ruin the rotation system?  Just because someone gains access to a zone does not mean that they have any ability to survive that zone.  Just like my analogy to your point of view earlier... if someone completes the Vex Thal key quest... it gives them ACCESS to the zone.  I don't care if they survive zoning in, or if they die upon zoning in.  It just gives them to ability to walk in.  There is no value to what is given except for the ability to access the zone.<br>
<br>
This in my opinion does not ruin anything.  Just because 2 guilds got a few people to join together to take down Arin-dar, Behemoth, Grummus... WHICHEVER POP Mobs to gain access to the next tier zones.  It garners them another zone to move into.  In no way should it ruin the spirit of the rotation system.<br>
<br>
How can it?  Why does it?  If you get flagged for another zone by killing said mob, what gives you incentive to go after him again?  With the exception of helping other guildmates/friends get flagged there is none that I know of.  Said mobs don't drop any loot.  They don't drop any plat that's worth doing them again.  All it does is allow someone access to another zone.  Just like Fear, Hate, Sky, and any PoP zone that requires you to be a certain level to enter.  Step into these zones alone and chances are you are going to die if you are not prepared.<br>
<br>
Hell, what says someone like myself, who's in a guild that finally got onto their very first rotation mob recently, gathers 72 (or so) people from all walks of life and guilds and takes down Arin-Dar, Behemoth, Grummus and is now flagged for that next zone.  Where's the difference?  How is it different?  Why is it different?  Again, all it would allow me to do is get into that zone.<br>
<br>
Rotation mobs be damned, there is NO comparison.  What it seems you want done is you want these mobs Rotation mobs so you can keep people out until they EARN the right to step inside that zone.  What gives you the right to control where and when I go?<br>
<br>
We have set up the Rotation system for specific mobs to allow others the chance at said mobs.  There are certain zones that are reserved by guilds/alliances so that there are chances that not everything will be killed when they step inside.  But these zones are not reserved 24/7 so people can still step inside them on those days that they are not reserved and have at whatever they may choose to attempt.  Making PoP Flag mobs Rotation mobs takes away any chance for someone who does not have the ability to get flagged unless he gets assistance by killing said PoP flag mobs the ability to step into those zones.<br>
<br>
You don't want me in there because I can't take care of business myself?  Then by all means perma kill the stupid things.  I've got the feeling that if you make these mobs rotation mobs people will ignore this system on these mobs.  IT'S THE WRONG THING TO DO!!!<br>
<br>
Probably repeated myself over and over, but you've got me angry and I'm surprised I didn't flame.<br>
